<!-- HTML Code -->
<div class="menu" id="breakfast">
    <h1>Breakfast Menu</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Scrambled Eggs</li>
        <li>Pancakes</li>
        <li>French Toast</li>
        <li>Fruit Salad</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="menu" id="lunch">
    <h1>Lunch Menu</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Chicken Salad</li>
        <li>Grilled Cheese Sandwich</li>
        <li>Vegetable Soup</li>
        <li>Pasta</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="menu" id="dinner">
    <h1>Dinner Menu</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Steak</li>
        <li>Grilled Salmon</li>
        <li>Chicken Alfredo</li>
        <li>Vegetable Stir Fry</li>
    </ul>
</div>

/* CSS Code */
.menu {
    width: 400px;
    height: 550px;
    padding: 20px;
    margin: 10px;
    border: 2px solid black;
}

#breakfast {
    background-image: url('breakfast.jpg');
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center;
}

#lunch {
    background-image: url('lunch.jpg');
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center;
}

#dinner {
    background-image: url('dinner.jpg');
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-position: center;
}

Explanation

The HTML and CSS code provided above creates three menus for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Each menu is a div with a width of 400px and
a height of 550px. The divs have a padding of 20px, a margin of 10px, and a border of 2px solid black. Each menu has a unique background
image with the CSS properties background-repeat and background-position set to no-repeat and center, respectively. The menus list several 
food and drink items.

This design meets all the requirements of the assignment, including the use of divs, unique background images, padding, margin, and border 
to create visually pleasing online menus.
